<br>
Axiom Shift is primarily a raiding guild. We have an agressive raiding schedule. We try to do things that challenge us in game and at the same time offer a good risk vs reward outcome. There is also the time factor.<br>
<br>
We generally raid in eastern standard time zone hours during the week.  This usually runs from 6pm eastern until midnight eastern. Weekends can be pretty flexible.<br>
<br>
The minimum level for the guild is level 63. While we don't have any real restrictions based on aa pts, flags, and such  those persons who are higher in level, posses more aa pts, and have a greater number of flags will be considered above those who do not.<br>
<br>
We currently are recruiting for all classes except Druids and Paladins.<br>
<br>
Classes that are a **need** class at the moment are:<br>
<br>
Enchanters<br>
Warriors<br>
Clerics<br>
Wizards<br>
<br>
The above classes are what we deem a top priority at the moment. The following classes have openings as well.<br>
<br>
Mages<br>
Rogues<br>
Monks<br>
Bards<br>
Necromancers<br>
Beastlords<br>
Shadowknights<br>
Shaman<br>
<br>
We try very hard to balance the guild so that we are not over stacked in one class. The only exception to this is of course is Clerics. As we are primarily a raiding guid it is important that we have a good contingent of healers. This is done so that people can feel useful. It also helps from a gearing up stand point including spells. Gearing up and getting spells for 12 Druids is just not something that is needed.<br>
<br>
We are not what most would deem an uber guild. If you are &quot;only&quot; looking to raid you might try a guild like Ascent, Echoes in Eternity, Dol Amroth, and or Arirang. <br>
<br>
If you are looking for loot, then you have come to the wrong place. Axiom Shift is not interested in any individuals who are only interested in gearing up. This is not to say we do not gear up. We just are a patient guild and try to do things that are best for the guild as a whole and not an individual. <br>
<br>
We try to do most encounters in game with less people then many guilds on Rodcet Nife. This make each person at that particular raid important to the success of the raid. This is the way we prefer to play.<br>
<br>
We currently have a goal of trying to reach a number of 36-42 people per raid. This allows us a good selection of targets to hit.<br>
<br>
We do have a standard raiding channel that we use.<br>
<br>
If you are interested in applying to Axiom Shift please contact either myself (Fargus) or Nestira in game.<br>
<br>
The way that it works is we will take some time to chat with you. If after talking with us you are still interested in seeing what Axiom Shift is about then you can join us as a guest on a raid.<br>
<br>
As a guest you will only be allowed to join in lotto's that are deemed an open lotto. Open lotto's are random 1 100 with 69 being an automatic win. You would be eligible for gifts and or hand me downs if that is stated.<br>
<br>
After you have adventured with us a few times if you feel that Axiom Shift is indeed a guild you would like to apply to then we can start probation for you. This will include an invite to the guild. <br>
<br>
The probation period is for 30 days. During this time you must be anonymous. As we take the guild tag seriously you must earn the right to fly it above your head. There are no exceptions to this rule. <br>
<br>
While on probation you are still considered a guest and are only allowed to participate in lotto's that are deemed an open lotto.<br>
<br>
After you are put on probation a forum is started with your name. People are encouraged to speak openly about you. Things that will be discussed are attendance, personality, and skill level. <br>
<br>
We are looking for active people. Humor plays a big part of the guild. If someone is active, is a good match from a personality stand point, but lacks the skill that most of the guild posses, as long as that person listens and demonstrates the ability to learn they will be considered.<br>
<br>
We want people who want to participate. This includes raids and groups. We tend to keep to ouselves and dont use pick up groups to much. We are not looking for individuals or what we would call a &quot;loner&quot;. We are looking for people who want to help the guild in all aspects of the game.<br>
<br>
If you don't like to group with guildmates and prefer to solo, duo, or use pick up groups all the time, then Axiom Shift is not the guild for you.<br>
<br>
Any one who is below level 65 and is put on probation must gain at least 1 level while on probation. If at the end of your 30 days you are still the same level you were at when you were placed on probation, you will be turned down for membership to the guild.<br>
<br>
After your probation period if your still interested in the guild and you have the needed support to get into the guild you will be welcomed into the guild and be allowed to fly  above your head.<br>
<br>
If you do not have the needed support at the end of the probation period you will be disbanded from the guild and no other reason will be given. It is not our place to try and break someone down by criticizing them. <br>
<br>
We know and understand that we are not a match for everyone. We will thank you for the help you provided us and wish you the best.<br>
<br>
<br>
If you are interested in the Axiom Shift please feel free to start a new thread and introduce yourself. It can be as generic as you like or as information filled as you feel necessary.<br>
<br>
Fargus Fabiyus<br>
Guild Leader<br>
Axiom Shift<br>
